# Ollama Model Pull List (OPTIONAL OVERRIDE)
#
# This is an EXAMPLE/template. By default the installer uses the built-in model
# profile (-ModelProfile Desktop = the six production models, coherent with
# config\crush.json + the launcher aliases). You do NOT need this file.
#
# To override the profile's pull list, copy this file to `ollama-models.txt`
# (drop the .example suffix) and list one Ollama tag per line. When that file
# exists, the installer pulls THESE tags instead of the profile's models.
#
# IMPORTANT: the launcher aliases (qwen36-27b-212k, qwen3coder-144k, etc.) are
# built FROM specific base tags in install-windows.ps1. If you change the pull
# list here, make sure the base tags the aliases reference are still pulled, or
# those aliases (and the crush.json / launcher entries that use them) will break.
#
# Tags correspond to Ollama library entries: https://ollama.com/library
# The hf.co/... tags are pulled via Ollama's HuggingFace passthrough.

# ── Production roster (the default profile; shown here as a reference) ──────────

# hf.co/unsloth/Qwen3.6-27B-MTP-GGUF:Q4_K_M   # Heavy coding default (Qwen3.6 27B+MTP), ~16 GB
# qwen3.6:35b        # Heavy coding / multimodal (Qwen3.6 35B-A3B), ~22 GB
# gemma4:31b         # Heavy coding / general (Gemma 4 31B), ~20 GB
# qwen3-coder:30b    # Light coding / review (Qwen3-Coder 30B-A3B), ~18 GB
# glm-4.7-flash      # Agentic / all MCP+tools (GLM-4.7-Flash), ~18 GB
# qwen3:8b           # Image-gen companion, ~5 GB
